Given, Discharge, [latex] \mathrm{Q}=10 \mathrm{MLD} [/latex] Detention period, [latex] \mathrm{t}_{\mathrm{d}}=2 \mathrm{hr} [/latex] Over flow rate, [latex] \mathrm{V}_{0}=40,000 [/latex] litres [latex] / \mathrm{m}^{2} / [/latex] day [latex] \mathrm{H}= [/latex] ? As, Surface area of tank [latex] =\frac{\text { Discharge }}{\text { Over flow rate }}=\frac{\mathrm{Q}}{\mathrm{V}_{0}} [/latex] So, [latex]
\begin{aligned}
& \text { S.A. }=\frac{10 \times 10^{6} \mathrm{~L} / \text { day }}{40,000 \mathrm{~L} / \mathrm{m}^{2} / \text { day }} \\
& \text { S.A }=250 \mathrm{~m}^{2}
\end{aligned}
 [/latex] Volume of tank [latex] (V)=Q \times t_{d} [/latex] [latex]
\begin{aligned}
& =\frac{10 \times 10^{6} \times 10^{-3}}{24} \times 2 \mathrm{~m}^{3} \\
& \mathrm{~V}=833.33 \mathrm{~m}^{3}
\end{aligned}
 [/latex] Hence, Height of water in tank or  Height of setting zone [latex]
\begin{aligned}
H & =\frac{833.33 \mathrm{~m}^{3}}{250 \mathrm{~m}^{2}} \\
H & =3.33 \mathrm{~m}
\end{aligned}
 [/latex] Note: In reality, height of water in tank OR height of settling zone is estimated by above approach but if the bottom of sedimentation tank is assumed to be sloping or hoppered (i.e sludge zone is also considered) then height of water in tank is determined as follows: Using, Volume of tank [latex] (V)=D^{2}\left(\frac{\pi}{4} H+0.011 D\right) [/latex] As, [latex]
\begin{aligned}
\text { S.A. } & =\frac{\pi}{4} D^{2}=250 \mathrm{~m}^{2} \\
D & =17.835 \mathrm{~m}
\end{aligned}
 [/latex] So, [latex] 833.33=(17.835)^{2}\left(\frac{\pi}{4} H+0.011(17.835)\right) [/latex] So, [latex] \mathrm{H}=3.085 \mathrm{~m} [/latex]

