& =11 \mathrm{Kg} / \mathrm{m}^{3}
\end{aligned}
[/latex] At 2-2, For [latex]\mathrm{R}_{5}[/latex] [latex]\mathrm{Q}_{5}=\mathrm{Q}_{3} \mathrm{Q}_{4}=10-3=17 \mathrm{~m}^{3} / \mathrm{sec}[/latex] [latex]\mathrm{C}_{5}=\mathrm{C}_{3}=11 \mathrm{Kg} / \mathrm{m}^{3}[/latex] At 3-3 for [latex]\mathrm{R}_{7}[/latex] [latex]
\begin{aligned}
\mathrm{Q}_{7} & =\mathrm{Q}_{6}+\mathrm{Q}_{5}=17+8=25 \mathrm{~m}^{3} / \mathrm{sec} \\
\mathrm{C}_{7} & =\frac{\mathrm{Q}_{6} \mathrm{C}_{6}+\mathrm{Q}_{6} \mathrm{C}_{5}}{\mathrm{Q}_{6}+\mathrm{Q}_{5}} \\
& =\frac{8 \times 10+17 \times 11}{8+17}=10.68 \mathrm{Kg} / \mathrm{m}^{3}
\end{aligned}
[/latex] Answer : [latex]10.6 \mathrm{~kg} / \mathrm{m}^{3}[/latex].

